<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-03-20</DATELINE><TITLE>Virus Infection and Titration of SARS-CoV in Mouse Lung</TITLE><BODY>Two critical steps when investigating an animal model of a virus infection are consistently successfully infecting animals and accurately determining viral titers in tissue throughout the course of infection. Here we discuss in detail how to infect mice with SARS-CoV and then quantify the titer of virus in the lung.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>